flowRoot.flowPara: * First, set the target temperature on the temperature controller to 64 C (see recipe).
* Set the target temperature on the urn to 80 C
* Close the valve on the urn and disconnect the hose to the pump. Move it to the connector on the mash tank. Connect the hoses to the copper coil in the urn (see picture).
* Connect the temperature controller to the pump with the thermometer in the mash tank
* Keep adding boiling water from a kettle to the urn, (it will need filling almost to the top).
* Keep stirring the mash with the big paddle.
